'''José Manuel Alberto López''' (born 6 December 2000), commonly known as '''Flaco López''', is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
López started his career at the age of seven with Club El Progreso in [[Saladas, Corrientes|Saladas]].<ref name="FG1"/> Six months later, soon before a trial in front of their scouts, the player was signed by [[Boca Juniors]].<ref name="FG1"/> At the age of nine, López joined [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]]; remaining until 2016, he notably trained with [[Ariel Holan]]'s first-team squad at one point.<ref name="FG1"/> 2017 saw López head to [[Club Atlético Lanús|Lanús]], initially featuring at youth level before being called up mid-season ahead of the [[2018–19 Argentine Primera División|2018–19 Primera División]] resumption.<ref name="FG1"/> However, in that period, López was loaned to [[List of regional football leagues in Argentina#Buenos Aires|Liga Tresarroyense]] side Colegiales de Tres Arroyos in 2019.<ref name="FG1"/><ref name="LVDP1">{{cite news|title=José López, de Colegiales: "Estamos muy motivados y confiados"|url=https://lavozdelpueblo.com.ar/noticia/84869-Jos%C3%A9-L%C3%B3pez,-de-Colegiales:-%E2%80%9CEstamos-muy-motivados-y-confiados%E2%80%9D|accessdate=4 January 2021|work=La Voz del Pueblo|date=7 July 2019}}</ref><ref name="LU1">{{cite news|title=Colegiales presentó las nuevas incorporaciones|url=https://www.lu24.com.ar/colegiales-presento-las-nuevas-incorporaciones/|accessdate=4 January 2021|work=Lu24|date=5 April 2019}}</ref> He finished his stint there as the club's top scorer.<ref name="FG1"/>

López was promoted into [[Luis Zubeldía]]'s senior squad in late-2020, appearing on the substitute's bench for [[2020 Copa de la Liga Profesional|Copa de la Liga Profesional]] encounters with [[Club Atlético Aldosivi|Aldosivi]] and [[Defensa y Justicia]].<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="IN1">{{cite news|title=Por una mínima ventaja Lanús se lleva los tres puntos ante Aldosivi|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2020/12/13/aldosivi-recibira-a-lanus-por-la-grupo-a-fecha-1/|accessdate=4 January 2021|work=Infobae|date=13 December 2020}}</ref> López, in the aforementioned competition, made his professional debut on 3 January 2021 during a draw on the road against [[Club Atlético Patronato|Patronato]], after he was substituted on in place of [[Gonzalo Torres]] with twenty-five minutes left.<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="LAN1">{{cite news|title=Lista de viajeros a Paraná|url=http://clublanus.com/secciones/futbol-profesional/noticias/lista-de-viajeros-a-parana|accessdate=4 January 2021|work=Lanús|date=2 January 2021|archive-date=26 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126011700/http://clublanus.com/secciones/futbol-profesional/noticias/lista-de-viajeros-a-parana|url-status=dead}}</ref> On his second appearance, López scored his first goal during a win over [[Rosario Central]] on 9 January.<ref name="Soccerway"/>

